title: For Sale:  Pre-64 Winchester Model 70  .270 WIN
postcontent:
Winchester Model 70 "Featherweight" .270 Win - manufactured 1955.
Includes Weaver K 2.5 Series 60 scope with "Lee Dot", single dot reticule,  by TK Lee

“Pre-1964” rifles had an action considered superior to later rifles. After 1964, this feature was dropped to reduce cost.

This is a very well-respected hunting rifle, especially for deer.  Its light weight gives it more recoil than a heavier gun, but for hunting, when you may carry the gun through the woods all day and only fire once, this is a good tradeoff. The gun also has smooth trigger action and nice woodwork with cut (not pressed) checkering. 

The Winchester Model 70 has an iconic place in American sporting culture and has been held in high regard by shooters since it was introduced in 1936, earning the moniker "The Rifleman's Rifle"  (p239 Bolt Action Rifles by Frank de Haas, DBI Books INC, Northfield ILL, USA, 1971)

This gun has not be used since the early 1960's. I inherited it from my father.
